{
  "stem": "734.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "So this became eventually-- these things became sort of a way of life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And you got adjusted to it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Radom?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Before the war, there was about 25,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And during the war, a lot of other Jews came in, Jewish families came in from different towns, surrounding towns, when they established the ghetto, especially.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I would say we had in excess of probably about 35,000 at s-- at one point during the, the war.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The deportation in August of '42 must have ta-- must have taken away, I would say, a good 30,000 or more Jews at a time.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they left maybe a little over 3,000 we were left at that time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These were Jews who were employed, who had steady jobs for the Nazis, you know, for the war industry.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like there were-- at the other end of town, there was a labor camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You remember [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Three Eggs, ?] where my father was?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my brother was there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was still working for this other studio, not the Orensteins, but the studio which was owned by-- after the Orenstein Studio was confiscated, I, I was lucky enough to get into a studio which was owned by a Polish man who was married to a German woman.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So therefore, they became German nationals.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she had privileges.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as such, being German, what they called [GERMAN SPEECH], of German ancestry, she had privileges to the point where they could-- she, she was able to employ Jews at the studio.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as a result, she employed three, three of us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we would have to be escorted from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was already after the ghetto was cut down in size to a couple of streets.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
